UID:ClpmhC7lyRjr4qExxsqvC
SUMMARY:Free Tax Help
DTSTAMP:20260325T064008Z
DTSTART:20260329T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Sunday\, March 29\, 2026\, 11am - 2:30pm\n\nTrained volunteers 
	will be available to answer questions and prepare personal tax returns.\n\
	nLocation Link:\n\nQueen Anne Branch\n\nRoom Location: Meeting Room\n\nReg
	istration Required: Registration is not required.\n\nDetailed Description:
	 This service is free and available to individuals only. The free service 
	is not available for business tax returns. To receive tax help\, bring the
	 following documents:\,\n\nRequired:\n\nPhoto identification\, Social Secu
	rity cards or Individual Taxpayer Identification Numbers \\(ITIN\\) for ev
	eryone listed on the tax return.\, Proof of income\, for example\, W2s and
	 1099s \\(Social Security benefits\\)\, Official documents on Social Secur
	ity Administration letterhead\, Medicare card \\(if Social Security number
	 is followed by an "A"\\)\, Be prepared to provide information about healt
	h care coverage for each person on the return.\,\n\nRecommended:\n\nLast y
	ear&'s tax return\, if available\, Bank account and routing numbers for di
	rect deposit of refunds\, Photocopies or computer print-outs of any of the
	se documents willbe accepted.\, Due to federal budget cuts the IRS is unab
	le to provide the Library with certain tax forms and instruction booklets.
	\, Most IRS forms are available online at\n\nwww.irs.gov .\, You may make 
	free black-and-white prints of the forms from Library computers:\n\nwww.sp
	l.org/Print \, Thanks to our partner\n\nAARP .\n\nEvent Logistics: AARP Ta
	x Help locations serve anyone who earned less than $80\,000 in 2025.\, For
	 eligibility details\, contact AARP at 888-227-7669.\n\nContact Us: If you
	 have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nA
	DA Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for people with disabilit
	ies at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days before
	 the event to request accommodations.\, All Library programs are free and 
	open to the public.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-
	tax-help/18162991/2026-03-29T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Learning & Education
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/20
	26-03-29T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-learning
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Learning & Education
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:dcolP9EUkml0_GZ5l3Mg5
SUMMARY:Free Tax Help / Ayuda gratuita con los impuestos
DTSTAMP:20260325T064008Z
DTSTART:20260329T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Sunday\, March 29\, 2026\, 11am - 5pm\n\nTrained volunteers wil
	l be available to answer questions and prepare personal tax returns.\n\nSp
	anish support may be provided per request.\n\n----------------------------
	------------------------------------\n\nVoluntarios capacitados estarán di
	sponibles para responder preguntas y preparar declaraciones de impuestos p
	ersonales.\n\nSe puede proporcionar ayuda en español a pedido.\n\nLocation
	 Link:\n\nSouth Park Branch\n\nRoom Location: Meeting Room / Sala de reuni
	ones\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not required / No se requie
	re inscripción.\n\nDetailed Description: This service is free and availabl
	e to individuals only. The free service is not available for business tax 
	returns.\, To receive tax help\, bring the following documents:\,\n\nRequi
	red:\n\nPhoto identification\, Social Security cards or Individual Taxpaye
	r Identification Numbers \\(ITIN\\) for everyone listed on the tax return\
	, Proof of income\, for example\, W2s and 1099s \\(Social Security benefit
	s\\)\, Official documents on Social Security Administration letterhead\, M
	edicare card \\(if Social Security number is followed by an "A"\\)\, Be pr
	epared to provide information about health care coverage for each person o
	n the return\,\n\nRecommended:\n\nLast year&'s tax return\, if available\,
	 Bank account and routing numbers for direct deposit of refunds\, Photocop
	ies or computer print-outs of any of these documents will be accepted.\, D
	ue to federal budget cuts the IRS is unable to provide the Library with ce
	rtain tax forms and instruction booklets.\, Most IRS forms are available o
	nline at\n\nwww.irs.gov. \, You may make free black-and-white prints of th
	e forms from Library computers:\n\nwww.spl.org/Print \, Thanks to our part
	ner\n\nUnited Way of King County .\,\n\n----------------------------------
	------------------------------Este servicio es gratuito y solo está dispon
	ible para personas individuales. El servicio gratuito no está disponible p
	ara declaraciones de impuestos de empresas.\, Para recibir ayuda fiscal\, 
	traiga los siguientes documentos:\,\n\nDocumentos necesarios:\, Tarjetas d
	el Seguro Social o Números de Identificación Fiscal Individual \\(ITIN\\) 
	de todas las personas que figuran en la declaración de impuestos\, Prueba 
	de ingresos\, por ejemplo\, formularios W2 y 1099 \\(prestaciones del Segu
	ro Social\\)\, Documentos oficiales con membrete de la Administración del 
	Seguro Social\, Tarjeta de Medicare \\(si el número de Seguro Social va se
	guido de una "A"\\)\, Esté preparado para proporcionar información sobre l
	a cobertura sanitaria de cada persona que figura en la declaración.\,\n\nS
	e recomienda:\, La declaración de impuestos del año pasado\, si está dispo
	nible.\, Números de cuenta bancaria y de ruta para el depósito directo de 
	los reembolsos.\, Se aceptarán fotocopias o impresiones de computadora de 
	cualquiera de estos documentos.\, Debido a recortes presupuestarios federa
	les\, el IRS no puede proporcionar a la biblioteca ciertos formularios fis
	cales y folletos de instrucciones.\, La mayoría de los formularios del IRS
	 están disponibles en línea en\n\nwww.irs.gov .\, Puede imprimir los formu
	larios en blanco y negro de forma gratuita desde las computadoras de la bi
	blioteca:\n\nwww.spl.org/Imprimir \, Gracias a nuestro socio\n\nUnited Way
	 of King County .\n\nEvent Logistics: United Way Tax Help locations serve 
	anyone who earned less than $80\,000 in 2025 \\(or less than $96\,000 for 
	non-single filers\\).\, For eligibility details\, contact United Way at 20
	6-461-3700.\,\n\n---------------------------------------------------------
	-------Los centros de ayuda fiscal de United Way atienden a cualquier pers
	ona que haya ganado menos de 80\,000 dólares en 2025 \\(o menos de 96\,000
	 dólares para contribuyentes que no sean solteros\\).\, Para obtener más i
	nformación sobre los requisitos\, comuníquese con United Way al 206-461-37
	00\n\nContact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor
	 call 206-386-4636.\,\n\n-------------------------------------------------
	---------------Si tiene alguna pregunta sobre este evento\,\n\npregúntenos
	\n\no llame al 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommo
	dations for people with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactL
	EAP\n\nat least seven days before the event to request accommodations.\, A
	ll Library programs are free and open to the public.\,\n\n----------------
	------------------------------------------------Podemos ofrecer adaptacion
	es razonables para personas con discapacidad en los eventos de la bibliote
	ca. Póngase en contacto con\n\nLEAP\n\nal menos siete días antes del event
	o para solicitar las adaptaciones.\, Todos los programas de la biblioteca 
	son gratuitos y abiertos al público.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/event
	s/#/details/free-tax-help-ayuda-gratuita-con-los-impuestos/18061697/2026-0
	3-29T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Learning & Education
